Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Prosecuting attorney J J. Crawford in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jonathan J Aranda in court.  Attorney Stephen Michael Govin in court for Jonathan J Aranda. Defendant pleads guilty to counts 1&2. Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and adjudges defendant guilty. Upon motion of the state counts 3-5 are to be read-in. Court grants motion. Court orders PSI.  Minutes filed.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 09:00 am.

EFFECTIVE DATE OF THIS ASSIGNMENT IS AUGUST 1, 2022.

Defendant Jonathan J Aranda in court.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by DDA James Sempf.  Attorney Stephen Michael Govin in court for Jonathan J Aranda. Called @ 3:41 p.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for 2nd status. Record by Atty. Govin that he is still waiting on discovery from the State that has not been turned over - supplemental report and surveillance video. Court addresses state as to status of discovery. Response by Atty. Sempf that it appears the two items are still missing. Nothing in the file indicates when to expect remaining items. Court sets matter over to her call on July 28th to check status of discovery. Matter will be reassigned at that time and set before the assigned judge. Court in recess.
Status conference scheduled for July 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jonathan J Aranda in court.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by Atty. Vivien TenHaken.  Attorney Stephen Michael Govin in court for Jonathan J Aranda. Court sets as requested. Court in recess
Status conference scheduled for June 16, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
